Permanent adoration chapel from 6 a.m. to midnight every day and at night from Thursday to Friday Sunday masses: 10 a.m. 11:15 a.m. And 7 p.m. Weekday: 11:15 a.m. and 7 p.m. Every Wednesday outside school holidays: praise and worship evenings from 8:15 p.m. to 9:30 p.m. (see Photos) Numerous groups for young middle and high school students, scouting (ND de Gerson) + Ski Spi camps in February
Magnificent Catholic church! Right in the middle of the 16th arrondissement of Paris: the recent restoration beautifies this church even more!

Very pretty church to meditate and find calm with Christ. Blessed Sacrament in the evening on weekdays sometimes until 10 p.m. and thus find a moment of peace and rest with Christ.

In Gothic style, the construction of this church dates from 1900. It is wedged between the buildings of a small street, opposite the United Protestant Church of Passy Annonciation. It only presents a small heritage: some capital decorations, a modern organ, a few contemporary statues, a large stained glass window on the facade and that of Saint Pierre-Julien Eymard on the left side.
Beautiful church even if very simple, adoration all day long, always a lot of meditation.
